==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Turndown
<hw>Turn"down`</hw> <pr>(t⟦ucir⟧rn"doun`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of being turned down;</def> specif.
<fld>(Elec.)</fld>, <def>Designating, or pertaining to, an incandescent
lamp with a small additional filament which can be made incandescent
when only a small amount of light is required.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Made to wear with the upper part turned down;
<as>as, a <ex>turndown</ex> collar</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turndown</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Turndown
<hw>Turn"down`</hw> <pr>(t⟦ucir⟧rn"doun`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An act of refusing or of being refused; <as>as, to get
a <ex>turndown</ex> in an application for a job, a grant,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A decline in activity, especially business; a
downturn; <as>as, they expect a <ex>turndown</ex> in housing
construction in the fall</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turnep</ent>⟦br⟧
